        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 4:50PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 450 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Acres, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Ashland around 505 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
